occurrenceRemarks:
Adventive shrubs 0.5-1.5 meters tall, branches arching, seen wild in three sites, evergreen, leaves shiny, veins sunken, bulging between lateral veins, leaves 2.4-3.5 x 1.4-2.3 centimeters wide; 8-15 flowers/inflorescence; flowers 6.5-7.5 millimeters long; petals erect, pink, base red, mid-vein sometimes red, apex pale pink; 20 stamens; filaments pink-red, apex white; anthers white with pink sutures; 3-4 styles.
Reference specimen for illustration in Revision of Flora of the Pacific Northwest, WTU Herbarium, 2015.
locality: Junction of Eagleridge Drive and TransCanada Highway (Exit 2), south of Horseshoe Bay.
habitat: Mossy cliffs and balds; full sun; with Arbutus, Cytisus, Holodiscus, Amelanchier alnifolia, Pseudotsua, Danthonia, Selaginella.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Bushy clump 4.5 m tall in full mast, all nodes with flowers, even the apparent cane shoots from previous season; spikes purplish, mostly 6-7 cm long; plant visible on Google Earth Street View taken July 2014, but no flowers evident though plant is unusually bushy at that time; leaves turning dry on the margins and plant seems ready to exhaust itself.

occurrenceRemarks: Sparsely branched shrub 2 m tall with plenty of persistent orange-red fruit, 10-11 x 8-9 mm, that are starting to drop off; seeds 3 to 5 per fruit; few plants noted in openings in the residential area among natural Douglas-fir, cedar and arbutus forest.
locality: Metro Vancouver, West Vancouver, Horseshoe Bay, opposite 6570 Madrone Crescent, 550 m due west of ferry dock.
habitat: Mossy rocky knoll of natural lot being cleared for a new home; growing with Rubus armeniacus, Anthoxanthum odoratum, Polypodium glycyrrhiza, Sorbus aucuparia.

habitat: Cultivated; Private property garden inside wood fence near driveway.

occurrenceRemarks: Live plant collected from Horseshoe Bay and grown in a pot, picked for pressing July 15; it grew rather lax in shaded pot at home.

habitat: Base of concrete highway barrier in sandy accumulations with Draba verna.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Perianth bristles greater than achene, 6 counted on one fruit, filaments persistent on fruit; large patch.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Cypress Bowl Provincial Park, Yew Lake, northeast shore where trail skirts shore between the two picnic benches.
habitat: Apparently aquatic, in 20 cm of water at normal level, with Nuphar polysepala, Juncus supiniformis.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Plants reddish pink striped; few seen in one site only.
recordedBy: Frank Lomer, Su-hui Lomer, Judith Holm
locality: Squamish, 8.5 km due north of town centre, 1.1 km due west of Alice Lake, 142 m west of Highway 99.
habitat: Mature Pseudotsuga menziesii-Tsuga heterophylla forest with open moss carpet understory, with Corallorhiza maculata, Hypopitys monotropa.

occurrenceRemarks: Ca. 100-150 plants, all around the 2 m deep bog pool; pitcher leaves slightly pubescent externally in distal parts; assumed to be a persisting planted population; site discovered by Ryan Durand on June 13, 2016.
recordedBy: Frank Lomer, Su-hui Lomer, Judith Holm
habitat: Near popular trail, in sphagnum bog, with Rhododendron groenlandicum, Kalmia microphylla, Vaccinium microcarpum, Drosera rotundifolia, Carex pauciflora.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Several plants; stamens 3, seeds with appendages on both ends.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Cypress Bowl Provincial Park, Midway chairlift, at base.
habitat: Streamlet channel, with Juncus ensifolius, J. effusus, Lupinus polyphyllus.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Rhizomatous, rays light violet-purple, arrays rather erect, stems purplish, leaves light green, some auricluate; identity uncertain, perhaps Symphyotrichum novi-belgii or with novi-belgii introgression or from cultivated origins.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Cypress Bowl Road, west side, south of Hollyburn Lodge parking lot.
habitat: Gravel side road parallel to main road, with Anaphalis margaritacea, Hypericum perforatum.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Single clump with ca. 25 old fruiting stalks.
locality: West Vancouver, Highway 99 exit on Highway 1, 400 m east of Eagleridge Drive overpass.
habitat: Roadside gravel shoulder below rock cliff, with Rumex acetosella, Buddleja davidii, Danthonia sp., juvenile Acer macrophyllum, Pseudotsuga menziesii, Amelanchier alnifolia.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

habitat: Montain lake edge, associated with Tsuga mertensiana, Cupressus nootkatensis, Vaccinium spp., Rhododendron albiflorum.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Large patch; inflorescence nodding slightly in flower bud; plants frozen during pressing.
locality: District of West Vancouver, 80 m south of Highway 99 at Nelson Creek, 50 m southwest of train tunnel.
habitat: Flat cleared area near trail and railroad tracks.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Single leaning-spreading evergreen shrub, 1.5 m tall, with some spines and spine-pointed spur shoots, one remaining orange berry.
locality: West Vancouver, railroad tracks, 15 m west of The Dale.
habitat: Shallow moist ditch, in railroad track rocks, with Rubus armeniacus, Rubus spectabilis, Thuja plicata, Gaultheria shallon, Daphne laureola, Alnus rubra.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: 1 x 1 m patch of about 30 stems, 3 more patches in 200 x 200 m; spikes break with pressure, 3 spikelets per node, outer 2 on pedicels; glume awns 10 mm, lemma awns 7-15 (22) mm, anthers 2 mm, indehiscent; blades to 7 mm; rhizomes present, plants loosely clumped; sterile hybrid Hordeum brachyantherum (infrequent) x Elymus glaucus (noted in adjacent woods)
locality: Squamish River estuary, 1.8 km north of river mouth at end of Spit Road, 50 m east of Spit Road.
habitat: Slightly saline tidal marsh, with Potentilla anserina, Triglochin maritima, Elymus repens, Symphyotrichum subspicatum, Sonchus arvensis, Lathyrus palustris, Hordeum brachyantherum.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Dwarfed plant in exposed site; frequent in rocky sites in the area.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Horseshoe Bay, exit at Highway 99, 1.6 km south of ferry dock.
habitat: Highway excavation rock cliff, with Buddleja davidii, Danthonia californica, Pseudotsuga menziesii.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Low spreading bamboo, to 1 m tall in 15 x 3 m patch; apparently spread by garden refuse and very tenacious; leaves hairy.
locality: West Vancouver, 25 m north of Marine Drive and Howe Sound Lane.
habitat: Area between fence of residential home and railroad tracks, humus soil over bedrock with leaf litter, growing with Rubus armeniacus, Pseudostuga menziesii, Acer macrophyllum.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Large plants; blades 5.0 x 4.0 cm (3.8 x 3.2 maximum in FNA)
locality: Squamish River estuary, 450 m due southwest of Spit Road and Government Road junction, 50 m east of Spit Road.
habitat: Alluvial woods, in semi-shaded soft mud of drainage channel, with Symphyotrichum subspicatum, Bidens amplissima, Potentilla anserina, Carex lyngbyei.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Several patches; often buried and just the heads poking up through the sand.
locality: Squamish River, 1.5 km north of mouth at end of Spit Road, 200 m west of Spit Road.
habitat: Clean shifting sandbar, with Juncus balticus, Potentilla anserina.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Single shrub 0.5 m tall; petals erect, pink and cream.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Horseshoe Bay, 200 m east of Highway 99, 1.1 km south of ferry dock.
habitat: Mossy bedrock outcrop under power lines, with Holodiscus discolor, Cryptogramma acrostichoides, Digitalis purpurea, Rubus ursinus, Danthonia californica.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Low prostrate mounding shrub, 0.3 m tall, 2 m spread; no flowers or fruit; single plant spread by birds.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Highway 1, south side, 300 m east of Eagleridge Drive.
habitat: Rocky south facing bluff, under multi-stemmed Arbutus menziesii, with Pinus contorta.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: 20+ clumps over 10 m; flowering stem tops recurved in bud, plants somewhat glaucous and rusty coloured when exposed.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Highway 1, 15 m south of, 370 m east of Eagleridge Drive.
habitat: Pseudotsuga menziesii, Arbutus menziesii, Pinus contorta slope; on stable talus on mossy bedrock knoll, with Anthoxanthum odoratum, Danthonia californica, Rubus ursinus, Festuca rubra.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Common; sample of robust plants in semi-shade; styles 2.
locality: Squamish River estuary, 2.8 km north of river mouth at end of Spit Road, 90 m east of Spit Road.
habitat: Alluvial woods, in semi-shaded firm mud of drainage channel, with Symphyotrichum subspicatum, Agrostis gigantea, Potentilla anserina.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Several; lemmas glabrous, margins entire; anthers 1 mm; pedicels smooth.
locality: Squamish River estuary, 1.2 km north of river mouth at end of Spit Road, 120 m east of Spit Road.
habitat: Bare clay mud flat from dredgings, slightly saline, with Atriplex dioica, Carex lyngbyei, Plantago maritima.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: A few patches in the marsh; inflorescence sometimes with 6-9 flowers; corollas sometimes 4-lobed, mostly 3-lobed.
locality: Squamish River estuary, west side, 730 m west-northwest of river mouth at end of Spit Road, 20 m west of main river channel.
habitat: Tidal marsh, with Calamagrostis canadensis, Sidalcea hendersonii, Schoenoplectus acutus, Oenanthe sarmentosa, Sium suave, Cicuta douglasii.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Single clump from a decumbent base, anthers 1.5 mm.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Horseshoe Bay, 1.4 km due south of ferry dock.
habitat: Margin of excavated rock on east side of Highway 99 at Eagleridge Drive, on Pseudotsuga menziesii, Arbutus menziesii south facing slope, with Epilobium brachycarpum, Epilobium foliosum, Vulpia myuros.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Co-dominant for 30+ m in limited habitat, some dwarf plants at extreme bank margin; spike heads dark, plump; scales to 2 mm wide; proximal bract amplexicaulous (often torn by developing achene in subproximal bract); subproximal bracts with flowers or fruit; achenes yellowish, perianth bristles lacking.
locality: Squamish River estuary, west side, 570 m northwest of river mouth at end of Spit Road.
habitat: Eroded margin of bare sand and turf meadow, with Carex lyngbyei.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

locality: Metro Vancouver, Horseshoe Bay, Marine Drive, east side, between bus stop and Orchill Road.
habitat: Rocky roadside forest slope below Highway 99, with Acer macrophyllum, Buddleja davidii, Arbutus menziesii, Alnus rubra, Thuja plicata.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Few clumps, probably more up the cliff; plants in very early stage of flower buds, flowering stems sharply bent on top, facing downwards; specimens pressed, frozen and dried.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Marine Drive, 200 m west of West Vancouver Yacht Club marina.
habitat: Road cut rock cliff, with Cytisus scoparius, Anthoxanthum odoratum, Buddleja davidii.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: Petals yellow; two plants, probably washed down naturally from the mountains.
locality: Squamish River, 1.5 km north of mouth at end of Spit Road, 200 m west of Spit Road.
habitat: Tidal sandbar island, flooded at high tide, with Juncus covillei, Potentilla anserina.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

locality: Squamish River estuary, 1.2 km north of river mouth at end of Spit Road, 120 m east of Spit Road.
habitat: Bare clay mud flat from dredgings, slightly saline, with Atriplex dioica, Carex lyngbyei, Puccinellia pumila.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

occurrenceRemarks: One cluster 3 x 2 m partially covered by cut slash debris and old fallen branches; new shoot growth reddish; first and only site I have seen in Metro Vancouver.
locality: District of West Vancouver, Horseshoe Bay, 270 m east of Highway 99, 1.2 km south of ferry dock.
habitat: Dry Pseudotsuga menziesii, Arbutus menziesii forest margin at power line clearing, with Gaultheria shallon, Lonicera ciliosa, Cytisus scoparius, Holodiscus discolor, Salix scouleriana.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border

locality: Squamish River estuary, 860 m north-northeast of river mouth at end of Spit Road, 300 m east of Spit Road.
habitat: Tidal mudflat, in bare mud with Isolepis cernua.
Name: Biodiversity Squamish boundary is the northern section south to Porteau Cove PP Border
